<a href="http://nesdev.com/2C02%20technical%20reference.TXT" class="postlink">This document</a> (search for "Frame rendering details") has a detailed description of the scanlines rendered during a frame. The reason that a lot of documents have the NTSC resolution as 224 scanlines is that most NTSC TVs are unable to display the full 240 scanlines.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1345">CartCollector</a> — Sun Feb 01, 2009 9:55 pm</p><hr />
